remarks: Corollary of Pigeonhole Principle.  If ` A ` is finite and ` B ` is a proper subset of ` A ` , the ` B ` is strictly less numerous than ` A ` .  Stronger version of Corollary 6C of [Enderton] p. 135. (Contributed by NM, 22-Aug-2008.)
statement: php3 $p |- ( ( A e. Fin /\ B C. A ) -> B ~< A ) $.
